        ✅ English
        401 Unauthorized → Login required / invalid auth
        403 Forbidden → No permission
        419 Page Expired → CSRF token mismatch (Laravel specific)
        500 Internal Server Error → Server/code issue


        Example (Laravel 419 - AJAX issue)
            $.ajax({
                url: "/save",
                type: "POST",
                data: {
                    name: "test",
                    _token: $('meta[name="csrf-token"]').attr('content')
                }
            });


        Tamil
        401 → Login pannala / wrong authentication
        403 → Access permission illa
        419 → CSRF token mismatch (Laravel la common)
        500 → Server error / code problem
        
        👉 AJAX la 419 varum if CSRF token include pannala.



🔴 2. Eloquent Relationships
    ✅ English + Example
        class User extends Model {
            public function posts() {
                return $this->hasMany(Post::class);
            }
        }
Type	Meaning
hasOne	: One record
      Meaning: One record is related to one record.
      
      Example:
      
      One User → One Profile
      
      English:
      A user has only one profile.
      
      Tamil:
      ஒரு Userக்கு ஒரு Profile மட்டும் இருக்கும்.

hasMany	: Multiple records

      Meaning: One record has multiple related records.
      
      Example:
      
      One User → Many Posts
      
      English:
      A user can have many posts.
      
      Tamil:
      ஒரு Userக்கு பல Posts இருக்கும்.
      

belongsTo	: (Many to One / Parent) : Parent relation

      Meaning: Child belongs to one parent.
      
      Example:
      
      Many Posts → One User
      
      English:
      Each post belongs to one user.
      
      Tamil:
      ஒவ்வொரு Postவும் ஒரு Userக்கு சேர்ந்தது.
      
      👉 இது hasManyக்கு reverse
      

belongsToMany	: Many-to-many

      Meaning: Many records relate to many records.
      
      Example:
      
      Students ↔ Courses
      
      English:
      A student can enroll in many courses, and a course can have many students.
      
      Tamil:
      ஒரு Student பல Courses படிக்கலாம், ஒரு Course பல Students வைத்திருக்கும்.
      

hasManyThrough	Indirect relation

      Meaning: Access data through another table.
      
      Example:
      
      Country → Users → Posts
      
      English:
      A country can get posts through users.
      
      Tamil:
      Country → User → Post மூலம் Post data கிடைக்கும்.
      
      👉 Direct connection இல்ல, indirect



